race.comment: The keys chances clashed recently in a Saturday grade BM78. DANCE TO THE BOOM (3) over-raced in the middle stages then failed to run on as favourite last start in that race at Randwick. Back in midweek company for the third run back from a spell and McDonald takes the reins. Expecting her to show her best today. SWELTERING (5) travelled midfield but failed to make an impression when resuming in the same race last time out. Runner-up in the Australian Oaks last prep so she will be better over more ground, but still fresh enough to be competitive at this level. LA ROJA (4) picked up nicely in the run home in the aforementioned BM78. Doubt this will be run to suit but she is honest and should be thereabouts. SOCRAZYINLOVE (6) has won a couple at Goulburn since resuming. Tougher assignment today but she is progressing well and gets some weight relief. IT'S A WONDER (7) is a gun fresh performer who can win without surprising.
